HEADWORD: Sepulchre
<hw>Sep"ul*chre</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Sepulchered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr> or <conjf>Sepulchred</conjf>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Sepulchering</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr> or <conjf>Sepulchring</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.]</vmorph>
<def>To bury; to inter; to entomb; <as>as, obscurely
<ex>sepulchered</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And so <qex>sepulchered</qex> in such pomp dost lie⟦br⟧
That kings for such a tomb would wish to die.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sepulchral</ent>⟦br⟧
